definition.value: An omega-carboxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with one of the carboxy groups of oxalic acid.
A short-chain fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of pentanoic acid.
An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of phenylacetic acid.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of an alpha-D-glucopyranose residue and a D-galactofuranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->2) glycosidic bond
The S-phytanoyl derivative of coenzyme A.
An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of propionic acid.
A glycosylglycerol that is glycerol in which the hydroxy groups at positions 1 and 2 have been converted into the corresponding D-galactopyranoside and D-glucopyranoside derivatives, respectively.
